			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One possible reason why Castlevania 3 used the MMC5 is because the VRC6 (used in 悪魔城伝説 a.k.a. akuden a.k.a. CV3j) used a rather odd bank switching layout (16KB bank at 8000-BFFF, 8KB bank at C000-DFFF, last 8KB hardwired at E000-FFFF) which only the MMC5 was capable of reproducing (no other Nintendo mappers have 24KB worth of swappable banks; MMC1, MMC4, and MMC3/MMC6 have only 16KB worth).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

